Dole ne Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take bayarwa don samar da fasaha ta wucin gadi.
Kai-Fu Lee, mai bincike kuma masanin AI wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple ya ce, "Da zarar China ta kara yin amfani da hankali, Amurka za ta ninka kudaden da take kashewa a kan wannan fannin".
Wannan ya biyo bayan sanarwar da wasu sassan gwamnatin Amurka suka yi game da AI a lokacin da Amurka ba ta da dabarun AI.
A shekarar da ta gabata, kasar Sin ta bayyana shirin ta na zama kasa ta daya a fannin kirkire-kirkire na AI nan da shekarar 2030.
"Idan muka yi la'akari da cewa sauran ƙasashe suna baya a Amurka, ninki biyu na kasafin kuɗin bincike na AI zai zama kyakkyawan farawa, kuma za mu sami ci gaba na gaba a cikin AI", in ji Lee.
A wata hira da aka yi da CNBCD a wannan makon, Lee ya ce ninka kudaden zai ninka yiwuwar Amurka ta samar da babbar fasahar kere kere ta gaba.
Littafin Li, mai suna, AI Superpower: China, Silicon Valley, da New World Order, wanda Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne shugaban kamfanin Sinovation Ventures wanda ke zuba jari a Face+ wanda shine daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin kera kere-kere a kasar Sin.
A shekarar 1980 a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, ya yi bincike kan tsarin AI wanda ya lashe gasar Otello, babban dan wasan Amurka, kuma daga baya ya zama shugaban binciken Microsoft da kuma shugaban kamfanin Google.
Lee ya san game da gasar fasaha ta gwamnatin Amurka ta baya kamar Gasar Robotics Challenge ta Hukumar Kula da Ayyukan Bincike na Tsaro, kuma ya tambaye ni lokacin da za a yi gasar ta gaba don taimaka musu gano annabin da zai biyo baya.
Lee ya ce masu bincike a Amurka sukan yi aiki tuƙuru don samun tallafin gwamnati.
